    },
    {
      "key": "courseSlug",
      "value": "",
      "type": "string"
    }
  ],
  "item": [
    {
      "name": "Guide",
      "description": "Use this folder first. It explains what the backend does, how auth works in Postman, and the expected request order for common workflows.",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Guide - Collection Overview",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "description": "Overview for this collection.\n\nUse cases covered now:\n- Health check the backend\n- Register with OTP-based email verification\n- Sign in and inspect the current Better Auth session\n- Fetch and update the authenticated user profile\n- List or manage course categories\n- Browse public courses\n- Create, edit, delete, and submit instructor courses\n\nRecommended request order:\n1. Run Health\n2. Run Auth - Register With OTP Verification\n3. Run Auth - Verify Email OTP\n4. Run Auth - Sign In With Email\n5. Run Auth - Get Session\n6. Run Users -> Get My Profile to confirm session and capture user context\n7. Run Course Categories requests if you need a category\n8. Run Courses requests for instructor or public catalog flows\n\nModule map:\n- Health: readiness endpoint\n- Auth: OTP signup verification plus Better Auth session routes\n- Users: profile and learning summary\n- Course Categories: public taxonomy plus admin category management\n- Courses: public discovery and instructor draft management\n\nFuture use cases that will be added into this same collection:\n- Student checkout and enrollment\n- Lesson playback and progress tracking\n- Reviews and ratings\n- Admin moderation and reporting",
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/",
              "host": [
                "{{baseUrl}}"
              ],
              "path": [
                ""
              ]
            }
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "Guide - Auth And Session Usage",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "description": "Auth and session guide for Postman.\n\nImportant behavior:\n- Signup verification uses OTP routes under /api/v1/auth/*.\n- Protected business routes do not use bearer tokens in this project.\n- They depend on the Better Auth session cookie created by requests under /api/auth/*.\n- In Postman, keep cookies enabled and send auth requests from the same imported collection/workspace.\n\nSuggested auth flow:\n1. Auth - Register With OTP Verification\n2. Auth - Verify Email OTP\n3. Auth - Sign In With Email\n4. Auth - Get Session\n5. Protected requests under Users or Courses\n\nNotes:\n- If OTP expires, use Auth - Resend Verification OTP.\n- Google OAuth remains browser-driven and is not optimized here for Postman automation.\n- If session cookies are not being reused, inspect Postman Cookies for {{baseUrl}}.\n- Protected endpoints will return authorization errors until a valid session exists.",
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/",
              "host": [
                "{{baseUrl}}"
              ],
              "path": [
                ""
              ]
            }
          },
          "response": []
        }
      ]
    },
